President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to appoint Pamela Bondi of Florida to be a Member of the President's Commission on Combating Drug Addiction and the Opioid Crisis. He has also announced his nomination of James F. Geurts of Pennsylvania to be Assistant Secretary of the Navy, Research, Development and Acquisition; Carla Sands of California to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to Denmark; Rebecca Eliza Gonzales of Texas to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Kingdom of Lesotho; and Manisha Singh of Florida to be Assistant Secretary of State, Economic and Business Affairs.